No arrests have been made in connection with the case of two toddlers who were found dead in a refrigerator at Bankhara village in Kuruman in the Northern Cape. The two – aged four and five – went missing at the weekend and were found dead in a refrigerator in a yard opposite their homes. Northern Cape police spokesperson, Mohale Ramatseba says an inquest docket has been opened. Ramatseba says, “We have opened a case of inquest for further investigation. We would like to appeal to our communities to make sure that children don’t play around unused freezers or old cars.”